A link to join the meeting to personally present our comment will be sent to you prior to the start of the meeting.

Please limit written and oral remarks to three (3) minutes unless otherwise informed.

Have a safe Labor Day Weekend!
Our Meal Distribution Sites will be closed on Monday, September 7, in observance of Labor Day. The High School, Isbell Middle School, Glen City and Barbara Webster sites will have a make up day on Tuesday, September 8th and serve meals from 11am-1pm. The High School will stay open until 2pm.
Nuestros sitios de Distribución de Comidas estarán cerrados el lunes 7 de septiembre, debido al Día del Trabajo. Los sitios de la Preparatoria, Isbell, Glen City y Barbara Webster tendrán distribución el martes 8 de septiembre de 11 am-1 pm. La Preparatoria permanecerá abierta hasta las 2 pm.

post_text:
A message from our Child Nutrition Services regarding our milk distribution /Un mensaje de Nuestro Servicio de Nutricion sobre la leche distribuida

Ultra High temperature or UHT milk is ultra-Pasteurized milk that comes in sterilized containers. It is shelf stable UHT milk and can sit out unrefrigerated for about three months. Once the carton is opened, the milk should be refrigerated and has the same shelf life as other fresh milk. Chill before drinking for best flavor.

La leche de ultra alta temperatura o UHT es leche ultra pasteurizada que viene en envases esterilizados. Es leche UHT que puede sentarse sin refrigerar durante unos tres meses. Una vez abierto el envase, la leche debe refrigerarse y se mantiene igual que las otras leches frescas. Enfríe antes de beber para obtener el mejor sabor.

Notice of Board of Trustees Election
Santa Paula Unified School District - 3 (Three) Board Member Positions
Area 2, Area 4 and Area 5
Candidates must reside with the Designated Areas
Monday, July 13, 2020 –Declaration of Candidacy Begins
Friday, August 7, 2020 – Last day to Declare Candidacy
Candidacy Papers are available at:
Ventura County Elections Division, 800 S. Victoria Avenue, Ventura CA
Anyone interested in running for office please refer to the County Website VenturaVote.org. Or call (805)654-2664, for any questions. They are encouraging as much “Contactless Candidate Filing” as possible, and are heavily encouraging appointments. During the filing period we will update daily the Candidate List here = https://recorder.countyofventura.org/elections/elections/candidates-campaigns/candidate-list/. If you have any questions please feel free to contact us.

Regular Board Meeting Today 07 08 2020 at 6:00 p.m.
We continue to encourage the public to view the meetings via www.kadytv.net. Due to social distancing guidelines minimal seating is available for the public. Doors will open at 5:30 p.m. and seating will be available to the first 14 members of the public. post_text: The 2020 United States Census is how the government counts our population. It determines how billions of dollars in federal money will be spent on important services, including schools. It happens only once every ten years, so now is our chance to be sure we’re counted. The census has just nine simple questions and takes only a few minutes to finish. You can complete the census online at www.2020census.gov or by filling out the paper form that you may have received in the mail. Completing the census is required by law and your personal information won’t be shared with any other government agency. If you don’t complete the census, a government worker will be visiting your home to follow up. So complete the census today to be sure that Ventura County gets the resources it deserves. Again, the census website is www.2020census.gov. Thank you.

post_text:
Teacher Appreciation Week is celebrated in May every year, but this year will definitely look and feel a lot different in the wake of the COVID-19 pandemic.

On behalf of the Board of Trustees, Administration and Support Staff we would like to acknowledge all our District Teachers this week - who not only educate our students, but fill so many roles such as, listeners, role models, motivators and mentors!

With students now learning from home, teachers also had some quick learning to do. They had to figure out how to educate virtually. They’ve had to turn to technology and in many cases, dramatically modify lesson plans.

Wondering how to say "Thank you" this year? Send a note, record a video message, or send a special drawing, these can all be done via e-mail.
text:
Teacher Appreciation Week is celebrated in May every year, but this year will definitely look and feel a lot different in the wake of the COVID-19 pandemic.

On behalf of the Board of Trustees, Administration and Support Staff we would like to acknowledge all our District Teachers this week - who not only educate our students, but fill so many roles such as, listeners, role models, motivators and mentors!

With students now learning from home, teachers also had some quick learning to do. They had to figure out how to educate virtually. They’ve had to turn to technology and in many cases, dramatically modify lesson plans.

Wondering how to say "Thank you" this year? Send a note, record a video message, or send a special drawing, these can all be done via e-mail.

To minimize the risk to our employees and our families, we will be going to a once a week meal distribution model for the rest of the school year, similar to our neighboring districts. We will be distributing on Mondays from 10:30am-12:30pm at Glen City Elementary and Barbara Webster Elementary.
Please do not arrive early to pick up meals as this creates a line of cars and traffic backs up into the street.
We appreciate your full cooperation so that we can continue to provide meals for as many households as possible.

Para disminuir el riesgo para nuestros empleados y a nuestras familias, vamos a seguir repartiendo comidas una vez a la semana para el resto del año escolar, de acuerdo a otros distritos. Estaremos repartiendo comidas los lunes de 10:30am-12:30pm en las Escuelas Glen City y Barbara Webster.
Por favor, no llegue temprano para recoger las comidas, ya que esto hace una línea de coches y puede bloquear a la calle. Agradecemos su cooperación para que podamos seguir proporcionando comidas.

post_text: Congratulations to the Girls Basketball on a great season, our girls lost last night in a heartbreaking 57-58 defeat to San Jacinto Valley in a Division 5AA CIF quarterfinal game. We are proud of our ladies, they played hard and left everything on the court! Way to go lady Cardinals!

post_text: Congratulations to the SPHS Boys Soccer Team on a great season! They ended their season as CCL Champs and made it to the the CIF Div 4 Quarterfinals. The Cardinals fell yesterday 0-2 at home at home to a solid Norte Vista squad. Congratulations once again SPHS boys soccer, you’ve made our community proud! Thank you all who attended yesterday’s game, we had a strong showing cheering our players!
